m_q.target_metric: average rate of semi-major axis decay (km/day) for two periods: quiet period (May 1-4, 2024) and storm period (May 10-13, 2024)
filters: EPOCH between 2024-05-01 and 2024-05-04 for quiet period
EPOCH between 2024-05-10 and 2024-05-13 for storm period
sub_questions: Calculate semi-major axis from MEAN_MOTION using Kepler's law
Compute daily decay rate from semi-major axis changes over time
Average decay rates separately for quiet and storm periods

schema_conflicts: Both files have identical column structures and dtypes

scale_issues: MEAN_MOTION_DOT values are very small (e-05 to e-03)
BSTAR values are negative and small (e-03 to e-04)
ECCENTRICITY values are very small (e-04 to e-03)
cross_source_conflicts: Time periods are different but data structure is consistent

format_notes: Files contain TLE data with orbital elements
MEAN_MOTION_DDOT column appears to be all zeros
Files include both calculated fields (SEMIMAJOR_AXIS) and raw TLE data

constraints: mu = 398600.4418 km^3/s^2 must be used for Kepler's law
Semi-major axis must be calculated from MEAN_MOTION: a = (mu/(n*2π/86400)^2)^(1/3) where n is MEAN_MOTION in rev/day
Decay rate = Δa/Δt where Δa is change in semi-major axis and Δt is time difference in days
derived_filters: Ensure chronological ordering within each period
Filter to only include valid MEAN_MOTION values > 0
statistical_tests: Linear regression of semi-major axis vs time for each period
Check for outliers in MEAN_MOTION values
Verify temporal coverage within specified date ranges
output_format_requirements: Pair of numbers with units km/day
Precision appropriate for orbital decay rates (likely 4-6 decimal places)
